## Plan Summary

**Only one file is touched:** `common/chat.cpp`

### What gets added

**1. New handler function** — inserted at line ~1633 (immediately before `common_chat_try_specialized_template`):

```cpp
static common_chat_params common_chat_params_init_mistral_instruct_v3(
        const common_chat_template & tmpl,
        const autoparser::generation_params & inputs) {
    common_chat_params data;
    data.prompt = common_chat_template_direct_apply_impl(tmpl, inputs);
    data.format = COMMON_CHAT_FORMAT_PEG_NATIVE;
    auto parser = build_chat_peg_parser([&](common_chat_peg_builder & p) {
        return p.literal(inputs.generation_prompt) + p.content(p.rest()) + p.end();
    });
    data.parser = parser.save();
    return data;
}
```

**2. Detection branch** — inserted inside `common_chat_try_specialized_template` just before `return std::nullopt` (line ~1690):

```cpp
if (src.find("[INST]") != std::string::npos &&
    src.find("[SYSTEM_PROMPT]") == std::string::npos) {
    LOG_DBG("Using specialized template: Mistral Instruct v0.3\n");
    return common_chat_params_init_mistral_instruct_v3(tmpl, params);
}
```

### Key design decisions
- **Detection condition** `[INST]` present + `[SYSTEM_PROMPT]` absent correctly selects Nemo/v0.3-style templates while excluding Ministral 3, Mistral Small 3.2, and V7 (all of which wrap system messages in `[SYSTEM_PROMPT]` and are already handled or fall through correctly)
- **No preserved_tokens** — `[INST]`/`[/INST]` appear only in the prompt, not in model output
- **No tool/thinking machinery** — the v0.3 spec as described has neither
- **Pattern follows GigaChat v3** (the simplest existing handler) exactly
